<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>Zend_Controller_Response_Abstract::sendHeaders() doesn't modify the HTTP status code if there haven't been any other headers set. For example, if you call setHttpResponseCode(400), then sendHeaders(), the client will receive the default code instead of 400. The attached patch fixes this bug.</p>

